cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.FL 

This paper deals with the encoding of the lambda calculus into the pi calculus, which is a topic related to both logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the behavioral equivalence adopted in the pi calculus, which is a topic related to theoretical computer science (cs.TL). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of these encodings to various call-by-name lambda calculi, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and formal languages (cs.FL).
